title: Woman gives birth outside office lift

organizations.name: sungai petani community response squad movement

text:
Thursday, 23 February 2017 | MYT 10:56 AM Woman gives birth outside office lift 
A pregnant woman gave birth to a baby boy outside the lift of an office building in Shah Alam at 12.30am on Wednesday. 
Nurul Munira Husin, 32, safely delivered a 2.7kg baby prematurely at 37 weeks on the floor, with her seven-year-old daughter by her side. 
"My daughter just stood there and stared at me. Maybe she was afraid seeing her mother in such a situation," Nurul recalled the "funny" birth experience. 
Nurul said she began to feel contractions while at home and had alerted her husband to make a trip to the hospital. 
But they had to make a stop at the office, which was five minutes away, as she had left her medical record book in her office desk. 
While her husband, Isnawi Samingan, 39, went to get the book, she went to relieve herself in the toilet and was shocked that the baby's head was already coming out. 
"I dashed towards the lift, but the pain was getting intense. Worried that the baby might suffocate, I started to push," she said. 
Isnawi said the whole delivery process took less than 10 minutes and it was an unforgettable experience.
